HQGuide.texi
The documentation of HeadQuarters in Texinfo format. You can use the
MakeInfo program from Reinhard Spisser and Sebastiano Vigna to convert
it to plain ASCII file or to the AmigaGuide(R) hypertext format.

HQGuide.guide
The documentation of HeadQuarters in AmigaGuide(R) V39 hypertext format.
Note that AmigaGuide(R) V34 displays this file without problems, since all
unrecognized commands and attributes are simply ignored by
AmigaGuide(R).

HQGuide.doc
The documentation of HeadQuarters in ASCII with ANSI escape sequences.
You need a file-viewer able to handle ANSI escape sequences (like Leggi).

HQGuide.dvi
The Device Independent format. You can print it on your printer (with TeX).

HQGuide.ps.gz
The documentation in PostScript format. You need Ghostscript and Ghostview
to show this file. 

Usage: "gzcat HQGuide.ps.gz | ghostview -" 		to show the file
       "gzcat HQGuide.ps.gz | lp -d printername"	to print on a 
							Postscript Printer
Makefile.hq
Makefile for generating the various documentation types from the
documentation source file HQGuide.texi.

Uasge: "ls -s MakeFile.hq Makefile"
       "Make all"
